description:
The Report Run object represents an instance of a report type generated with
specific run parameters. Once the object is created, Stripe begins processing the report.
When the report has finished running, it will give you a reference to a file
where you can retrieve your results. For an overview, see
[API Access to Reports](https://stripe.com/docs/reporting/statements/api).

Note that certain report types can only be run based on your live-mode data (not test-mode
data), and will error when queried without a [live-mode API key](https://stripe.com/docs/keys#test-live-modes).

created.description: Time at which the object was created. Measured in seconds since the Unix epoch.

error.description:
If something should go wrong during the run, a message about the failure (populated when
 `status=failed`).

livemode.description: `true` if the report is run on live mode data and `false` if it is run on test mode data.

object.description: String representing the object's type. Objects of the same type share the same value.

columns.description: The set of output columns requested for inclusion in the report run.

connected_account.description: Connected account ID by which to filter the report run.

currency.description: Currency of objects to be included in the report run.

interval_end.description: Ending timestamp of data to be included in the report run (exclusive).

interval_start.description: Starting timestamp of data to be included in the report run.

payout.description: Payout ID by which to filter the report run.

reporting_category.description: Category of balance transactions to be included in the report run.

timezone.description: Defaults to `Etc/UTC`. The output timezone for all timestamps in the report. A list of possible time zone values is maintained at the [IANA Time Zone Database](http://www.iana.org/time-zones). Has no effect on `interval_start` or `interval_end`.

report_type.description: The ID of the [report type](https://stripe.com/docs/reports/report-types) to run, such as `"balance.summary.1"`.

anyOf.description:
This is an object representing a file hosted on Stripe's servers. The
file may have been uploaded by yourself using the [create file](https://stripe.com/docs/api#create_file)
request (for example, when uploading dispute evidence) or it may have
been created by Stripe (for example, the results of a [Sigma scheduled
query](#scheduled_queries)).

Related guide: [File Upload Guide](https://stripe.com/docs/file-upload).

created.description: Time at which the object was created. Measured in seconds since the Unix epoch.

expires_at.description: The time at which the file expires and is no longer available in epoch seconds.

filename.description: A filename for the file, suitable for saving to a filesystem.

links.description: A list of [file links](https://stripe.com/docs/api#file_links) that point at this file.

items.description:
To share the contents of a `File` object with non-Stripe users, you can
create a `FileLink`. `FileLink`s contain a URL that can be used to
retrieve the contents of the file without authentication.

created.description: Time at which the object was created. Measured in seconds since the Unix epoch.

expired.description: Whether this link is already expired.

expires_at.description: Time at which the link expires.

file.description: The file object this link points to.

livemode.description: Has the value `true` if the object exists in live mode or the value `false` if the object exists in test mode.

object.description: String representing the object's type. Objects of the same type share the same value.

url.description: The publicly accessible URL to download the file.

items.title: FileLink

has_more.description: True if this list has another page of items after this one that can be fetched.

object.description: String representing the object's type. Objects of the same type share the same value. Always has the value `list`.

url.description: The URL where this list can be accessed.

links.title: FileFileLinkList

object.description: String representing the object's type. Objects of the same type share the same value.

size.description: The size in bytes of the file object.

title.description: A user friendly title for the document.

type.description: The type of the file returned (e.g., `csv`, `pdf`, `jpg`, or `png`).

url.description: The URL from which the file can be downloaded using your live secret API key.

anyOf.title: File

result.description:
The file object representing the result of the report run (populated when
 `status=succeeded`).

status.description:
Status of this report run. This will be `pending` when the run is initially created.
 When the run finishes, this will be set to `succeeded` and the `result` field will be populated.
 Rarely, we may encounter an error, at which point this will be set to `failed` and the `error` field will be populated.

succeeded_at.description:
Timestamp at which this run successfully finished (populated when
 `status=succeeded`). Measured in seconds since the Unix epoch.

title: reporting_report_run
